      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Require evidence artifacts for run proofs",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add repeatable `--require-artifact <glob>` to `crabbox run` so a command that exits 0 can still fail when required proof files are missing\n- collect required artifacts through the existing run artifact tarball path and reject unsupported delegated/native targets clearly\n- document the new evidence guard in the run and artifact docs\n- add a Data Runs design plan that frames data work as a generic run-evidence pattern first, with a future `crabbox data` namespace only if the generic primitives prove too awkward\n- link forward-looking plans from the docs index\n\n## Context\n\nThe framing is intentionally generic. Public `crabbox.sh` describes Crabbox as remote execution with proof, and the OpenClaw-facing docs keep the agent contract around typed `run`/`warmup` tools rather than a domain-specific data product. `--require-artifact` supports data-run manifests, QA reports, and agent proof loops without making Crabbox own connectors, schedules, raw data, or warehouse semantics.\n\nRefs https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/225\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go test ./internal/cli`\n- `go test ./...`\n- `scripts/check-docs.sh`\n",
        "branch": "codex/data-runs-plan",
